article.headline: Northeastern 75, Stony Brook 69
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Jose Juan Barea scored 30 points and Northeastern beat Stony Brook 75-69 on Tuesday night in the America East Conference opener for both teams. Marcus Barnes added 15 points for the Huskies (4-4), while Shawn James had four points, 13 rebounds and six blocked shots. Cori Spencer had 15 points for the Seawolves (4-4), while Antawn Hardy and Mike Popoko each added 14. Hardy had nine points as the Seawolves opened the second half with an 18-5 run to take a 45-37 lead with 5:11 to play. Barnes had three 3-pointers and Barea added six points in the Huskies' 21-5 run that gave them a 58-50 lead with 8:53 to go. Two free throws by Hardy got Stony Brook within 66-65 with 1:20 left, but Barnes had four free throws as Northeastern closed the game with a 9-4 run.
